The Nigeria Federal Fire Service (FFS) on Tuesday announced the promotion of over 231 junior officers in recognition of their commitment to the mandate of the service. This is just as the entrance and premises of the FFS headquarters is wearing a new look following the ongoing renovation exercise of the red and yellow building.  The Controller General Federal Fire Service Engr. Joseph Garba Anebi, MIFireE, who announced the promotion during an event at its headquarters congratulated the newly promoted officers and urged them to keep up the good work. Details later.